1
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,130
There are so many beautiful things in this world,

2
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,880
but none of them belong to me.

3
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,240
God is so unfair.

4
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,130
You stay at home all day,

5
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:02,400
and you don't even care about our child's studies.

6
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,280
I did.

7
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,320
What did you do?

8
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,880
Her grades are getting worse.

9
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,610
Is this the result of your care?

10
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,120
I really did.

11
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,660
How dare you talk back!

12
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,680
Talk back? I'll show you!

13
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:14,480
Talk back!

14
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:18,560
Stop beating me! Please stop!

15
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:21,600
Get out!

16
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:45,760
I'll get the medicine.

17
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:46,600
No need.

18
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:48,640
Xiaoyan.

19
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,600
I don't understand why you won't get a divorce.

20
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,090
After every time this happens,

21
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,280
you just cry.

22
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,120
What's the use of crying?

23
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,520
If I get a divorce,

24
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,490
where would we live?

25
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,360
The money is with your dad.

26
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,720
He is not my dad.

27
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,180
I don't have a father like him.

28
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,560
Xiaoyan.

29
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,480
I'm sorry.

30
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,680
It's all my fault.

31
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:17,840
I'm sorry.

32
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,680
Just divorce him, okay?

33
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,840
I can quit school

34
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,320
and get a job.

35
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,360
We can rent a place to live.

36
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,280
The world is so big.

37
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,440
There must be a place for us.

38
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:35,920
No.

39
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:37,720
You have to study.

40
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,860
Once you get into college,

41
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,920
you can leave here.

42
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:43,480
What about you?

43
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,500
What will you do after I leave?

44
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:49,540
Half of your life has already been ruined by him.

45
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,640
Mom is fine.

46
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,440
Your dad will change.

47
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,680
He won't change, Mom.

48
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,079
I'm begging you.

49
00:03:57,600 --> 00:04:00,040
Let's leave here, okay?

50
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,680
I can go study in another city.

51
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,480
We can rent a place.

52
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:07,840
I can work part-time while studying.

53
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,760
You don't need to support me.

54
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,080
I can even support you.

55
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,360
I don't want to live like this anymore.

56
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,720
Mom, I'm begging you.

57
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:15,520
Really.

58
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:18,260
Mom, I really can't stand it for another second.

59
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:21,680
I'm begging you, let's go.

60
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:25,680
But I can't let you grow up without a father.

61
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,840
I can't let you be a child from a single-parent family.

62
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,040
Would that

63
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:32,360
be any worse than now?

64
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,400
But...

65
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,960
You still can't leave him, can you?

66
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:44,280
What are you holding onto?

67
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,320
How could you?

68
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,880
So cowardly.

69
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,880
Xiaoyan.

70
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:08,720
Xiaoyan.

71
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,040
Qiao Yan.

72
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,240
Yuanbao.

73
00:05:47,159 --> 00:05:47,890
You are here.

74
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:50,800
Yuanbao, don't be afraid. I am here.

75
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,200
Mutou.

76
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:01,720
Yuanbao.

77
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:03,840
Hold on.

78
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,730
Hold on tight behind me.

79
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,240
Yuanbao,

80
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:17,920
how are you?

81
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,360
I am back.

82
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:23,720
You are home. It's alright.

83
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,240
Bao, I made you some pork rib soup.

84
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,760
Get up and have some later

85
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,160
to regain your strength.

86
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,320
It will be ready soon.

87
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,560
I'll go check the soup.

88
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,960
Yuanbao, I'll pour you a glass of hot water.

89
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,320
I'm sorry, Grandma.

90
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,000
I made you worry.

91
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,280
Say no more. I know everything.

92
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,880
You know?

93
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,100
Qiao Yan was more conscious than you.

94
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:52,760
She told us everything.

95
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,290
You did the right thing.

96
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:57,320
You don't blame me?

97
00:06:57,880 --> 00:07:00,520
It'd be a lie to say I'm not angry or don't blame you.

98
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,240
But thanks to you this time,

99
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,440
otherwise Qiao Yan would be finished,

100
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:06,300
and their family would be broken.

101
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,560
My granddaughter is so brave.

102
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,400
By the way, how is Qiao Yan?

103
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:14,720
She's fine. She's gone home.

104
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,320
Gone home?

105
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:17,640
Don't worry.

106
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,840
Mr. Tian went back with her.

107
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,200
Speaking of Qiao Yan's father,

108
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,690
I'm really speechless.

109
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,840
How could he do such a thing?

110
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:28,280
No wonder Qiao Yan got depression.

111
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,800
And look at her mother,

112
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,480
so cowardly.

113
00:07:33,159 --> 00:07:34,690
I really don't understand.

114
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,440
Grandma.

115
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,760
I feel so lucky.

116
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,920
Having you is enough for me.

117
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:46,640
Here, Yuanbao.

118
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,100
Get up and have some water.

119
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,530
Come on, get up and have some water.

120
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:54,280
Here.

121
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,080
You sprained your hand. Don't move.

122
00:07:59,080 --> 00:07:59,880
Let me do it.

123
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:00,740
Here, Grandma.

124
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,040
Well,

125
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,600
I'll go help auntie cook. You guys talk.

126
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:25,980
What's wrong with you?

127
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,200
Nothing.

128
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,760
Were you worried about me?

129
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,200
Who's worried about you?

130
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,520
Don't flatter yourself.

131
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,720
Heartless.

132
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:46,600
Blockhead.

133
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:51,080
Well, I'll go help mom cook.

134
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,720
Don't you know

135
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,680
you almost lost your own life?

136
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,080
I'm sorry.

137
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,560
How is Qiao Yan?

138
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:24,300
She just took her medicine and went to sleep.

139
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,010
I don't mind you laughing at me,

140
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:28,960
but it's all our fault

141
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,320
that Xiaoyan

142
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,480
ended up like this today.

143
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,840
She is a good kid.

144
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:38,560
Unfortunately, she didn't have good parents.

145
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,420
Qiao Yan's father,

146
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:42,100
have you ever hit Qiao Yan?

147
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,200
It's all my fault.

148
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,840
It's because of the alcohol.

149
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,480
I swear I will never drink again.

150
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,760
I won't touch a drop of alcohol for the rest of my life.

151
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:53,680
I'm not human if I drink again.

152
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:02,040
Your promises could fill a book.

153
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,800
What's the point of saying all this?

154
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,160
Let's get a divorce.

155
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,880
What are you talking about?

156
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,660
Qiao Yan's mother.

157
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,280
I think

158
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:21,320
you two should talk calmly.

159
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,340
The top priority right now

160
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:24,940
is to untie Qiao Yan's knot

161
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,520
and cure her illness.

162
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,840
I was too weak before,

163
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:32,010
and failed to protect my daughter.

164
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,520
I will only live for Xiaoyan from now on.

165
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,520
As long as it's good for my daughter,

166
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,440
I'd even give my life.

167
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,860
Qiao Yan's father.

168
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,240
A man

169
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:57,000
who can bring himself to hurt his dearest wife and child

170
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,130
is truly heartless.

171
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,280
He doesn't even deserve to be called a man,

172
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:01,720
let alone a human.

173
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:04,770
That's all I have to say.

174
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,820
You're on your own now.

175
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:31,000
After modified electroconvulsive therapy,

176
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,560
some temporary memory loss does indeed occur.

177
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:35,120
But as time passes,

178
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,640
those memories will slowly return.

179
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,960
Don't worry too much.

180
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,800
Besides the phone,

181
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,520
I clearly wrote a few letters.

182
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,200
But...

183
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:54,040
What on earth did I write?

184
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,860
Why don't I remember anything at all?

185
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,060
Look outside the bedroom window!

186
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:14,720
Qiao Yan.

187
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,760
We love you.

188
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,680
We're waiting for you to come back to us.

189
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,600
Qiao Yan, we love you.

190
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:28,040
You are not fighting alone.

191
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,600
Qiao Yan, love you!

192
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,650
We are waiting for you to come back.

193
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:33,600
Qiao Yan.

194
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,880
We will always be your best friends.

195
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,040
Qiao Yan, we love you.

196
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,690
We will always be your strongest supporters.

197
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:43,760
Qiao Yan, remember the saying,

198
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:45,000
it's no big deal.

199
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:48,000
Stay strong, Qiao Yan!

200
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:50,600
Come on, Qiao Yan!

201
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:51,480
Qiao Yan,

202
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,240
eat well, drink well,

203
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,320
and don't let things bother you.

204
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,960
Stay strong, Qiao Yan.

205
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:58,280
You are the best.

206
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:57,880
Qiao Yan, we love you.

207
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:01,120
We will love you forever and ever.

208
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,460
Hello, little one.

209
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,800
Do you want a balloon?

210
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,280
Is a pink one okay?

211
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:52,680
Yes.

212
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:53,760
Okay, here you go.

213
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,680
God endowed humans with many abilities.

214
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,720
The greatest one is love.

215
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:38,160
It can melt glaciers and cross mountains and seas,

216
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:41,160
nourish all things, and create miracles.

217
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:43,760
Fortunately, we are still here.

218
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:47,040
Fortunately, love is still here.

219
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,640
I bought some fruits.

220
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:04,920
There are kiwis and dragon fruit that Xiaoyan likes,

221
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:05,840
and mangoes.

222
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,320
Remember to eat them.

223
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:15,880
By the way.

224
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:23,160
Here are the bank cards and the rest of the cash.

225
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,520
I'll leave them here for you two.

226
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:27,240
If,

227
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:30,680
after the New Year,

228
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:36,320
you still want to get a divorce,

229
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:39,920
I agree.

230
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:42,920
The house

231
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,480
and the money

232
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:48,240
will be left to you.

233
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:51,940
I will leave with nothing.

234
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:03,290
I'm leaving.

235
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:27,560
Did you call me?

236
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:37,640
It's so cold.

237
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,580
Where are you going alone?

238
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,080
Stay.

239
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,640
I'm sorry.

240
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:48,160
I'm sorry.

241
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:52,120
I'm sorry.

242
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,160
My father

243
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:51,440
is the best father in the world.

244
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:54,090
He would take me to the amusement park,

245
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,520
buy me cake,

246
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,800
help me with my homework,

247
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,360
and act like a clown to make me happy.

248
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,720
Every time I got sick,

249
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,920
Dad would stay by my side,

250
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,720
give me water and medicine,

251
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:13,040
and tell me a lot of jokes.

252
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:16,360
He was like an encyclopedia,

253
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:17,840
knowing everything.

254
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:25,320
But I don't know when it started,

255
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:28,020
Dad stopped smiling as much as he used to.

256
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,800
He no longer told me stories

257
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:32,080
or helped me with my homework.

258
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,120
He started drinking a lot

259
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:35,560
and losing his temper.

260
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:38,400
He didn't seem like my dad anymore.

261
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:41,320
My dad is gone.

262
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,640
I miss him so much.

263
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:49,200
I really want to find him.

264
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:16,050
Sweetheart.

265
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,280
Daddy's home.

266
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:22,640
I'm sorry. I'm late.

267
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:24,760
Don't worry.

268
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:27,160
I've pulled myself together.

269
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,360
I promise you,

270
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,760
I will never drink again.

271
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:37,680
I will love you with all my heart,

272
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:39,000
and your mom.

273
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:26,360
Forgive me, okay?

274
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:54,420
The first semester of junior year

275
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:56,560
ended with a bang just like that.

276
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:01,090
Some people have been here.

277
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:09,080
Some people have left.

278
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:23,200
Let's go, bro.

279
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:49,800
Some people remain the same.

280
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:53,440
But some people have changed.

281
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,840
Tomorrow is New Year's Eve.

282
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,160
Why are you still taking extra classes?

283
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:12,420
Doesn't your cram school have a holiday?

284
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:14,240
Don't mention it.

285
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:16,320
The cram school is on holiday.

286
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:17,580
My mom found me a tutor.

287
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:19,540
One-on-one, tutoring me at home.

288
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:22,080
If the teacher didn't have to celebrate the New Year,

289
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,160
I guess my mom would wish

290
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:25,560
I could have classes even on New Year's Eve.

291
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:28,120
Your mom is torturing you like this?

292
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,120
You know my parents.

293
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,880
They firmly believe that God rewards the diligent,

294
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:35,240
and no pain, no gain.

295
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:38,040
Didn't I drop three places in the exam this time?

296
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:39,300
Guess what my mom said.

297
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,720
My mom said if I don't make progress

298
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,840
in the next exam,

299
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:46,200
so she can just let me stay at the cram school and not go home.

300
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,280
Compared to that,

301
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:49,330
my grandmother is way more gentle.

302
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,640
That's why I envy you.

303
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,530
You two princesses,

304
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:58,300
the food is ready. Time to eat.

305
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:10,520
Wait for me downstairs after you finish eating.

306
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:12,120
I have something to tell you.

307
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,720
What a coincidence. I also have something to tell you.

308
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:15,440
Really?

309
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:17,720
See you later then.

310
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:31,960
Blockhead.

311
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,280
Ruirui went back.

312
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:37,170
Let's go. I'll take you somewhere.

313
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:38,880
Didn't you have something to say to me?

314
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:39,880
Where are we going all of a sudden?

315
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:40,880
Just come with me.

316
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:54,760
So late at night,

317
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:56,520
why did you bring me here?

318
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:57,900
Diamond Princess,

319
00:24:58,160 --> 00:25:00,760
do you still remember the promise we made at 18?

320
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,200
Diamond Princess.

321
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,360
Yuanbao, Yuanbao, don't cry.

322
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,480
Where are you hurt?

323
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:15,360
What's wrong?

324
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:17,400
Yuanbao, look.

325
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,920
Is that a diamond?

326
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,440
Where?

327
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:29,120
I've heard the story of the Diamond Princess.

328
00:25:29,120 --> 00:25:30,250
Have you heard of it?

329
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:31,680
Diamond Princess?

330
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:32,520
Yes.

331
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:34,640
A long time ago, there was a little girl.

332
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:37,480
Her tears could turn into shining diamonds.

333
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:39,880
So people called her the Diamond Princess.

334
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:42,480
One day, an old man with a white beard found her

335
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:45,160
and told her that when she turned 18,

336
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:47,120
if she brought her diamond tears

337
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,360
to the same place on the same day,

338
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:52,220
she would receive a mysterious gift from an elf.

339
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:53,800
What mysterious gift?

340
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:55,120
I don't know.

341
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,480
But look at your tears.

342
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:58,720
They've turned into shining diamonds.

343
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:01,280
That means you are also a Diamond Princess.

344
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:03,640
You have to keep this diamond safe.

345
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,320
When you turn 18,

346
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:06,840
we'll come back here.

347
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:07,680
Then we'll know

348
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:09,400
what gift the elf gives you.

349
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:12,920
You must come too.

350
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:13,800
Definitely.

351
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:15,940
Don't even mention it.

352
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:19,000
I treasured that piece of broken glass for a long time.

353
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:21,880
I even really thought it was a diamond at one point.

354
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,520
To get more diamonds,

355
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:26,160
I secretly cried countless times.

356
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:28,800
My eyes got swollen from crying so many times,

357
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,360
but I never succeeded once.

358
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:35,720
Actually,

359
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:37,400
this story

360
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:39,480
isn't completely fake.

361
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:40,680
What?

362
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:42,640
Are there really elves

363
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:44,370
delivering mysterious gifts?

364
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,480
Come on, try closing your eyes.

365
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:47,840
What for?

366
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,500
Just close them when I tell you to.

367
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:52,880
So mysterious.

368
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:09,680
The elf says

369
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,480
you can open your eyes now.

370
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:30,320
Studying?

371
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,320
Auntie.

372
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:35,200
Dad, Mom, what's wrong?

373
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:37,640
There's something.

374
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:39,240
Grandma, Dad, and I

375
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:41,340
have been discussing for a long time.

376
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:44,220
We want to hear your and Yuanbao's opinions.

377
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:49,520
What is it?

378
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:52,080
Honey,

379
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:53,740
let's sit down to talk.

380
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,200
Okay, let's sit down.

381
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:01,960
It's like this.

382
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:03,400
As you know,

383
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:06,520
your dad's previous job in the UK was pretty good,

384
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:08,640
and the salary was substantial.

385
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:11,100
But after returning to China,

386
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,280
up to now,

387
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,160
he hasn't found a suitable job.

388
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:17,760
You know our family's financial situation.

389
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:22,880
Seeing as you two are about to go to college,

390
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:25,800
the expenses will be huge.

391
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:27,640
So we discussed it

392
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:31,800
and decided to have your dad go back to the UK to work after the New Year.

393
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:32,600
This way,

394
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:35,400
our family's financial burden will be lightened.

395
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:36,520
Son.

396
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:38,320
I know.

397
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:41,200
I've been working out of town these years,

398
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:43,560
and I'm rarely home to accompany you.

399
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:45,320
Even when the accident happened last time,

400
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:46,760
I rushed back late.

401
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:50,560
Actually, I'm really conflicted.

402
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,180
Leaving you all at home

403
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:55,960
makes me feel really guilty.

404
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:58,680
Dad, just focus on your work.

405
00:28:59,120 --> 00:28:59,960
I support you.

406
00:29:00,080 --> 00:29:02,000
Yes, Uncle. I support you too.

407
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:06,440
Didn't you complain about your dad to me before,

408
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:08,560
saying he's always busy with work

409
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:09,920
and doesn't care about you?

410
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:10,600
This time,

411
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:12,480
why did you agree so readily?

412
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:16,360
I've grown up.

413
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:18,610
I'm definitely more sensible now.

414
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:21,520
Dad works outside for our family,

415
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:22,480
for Grandma,

416
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:23,530
and for Yuanbao.

417
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,160
I understand.

418
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:28,160
See? What did I tell you?

419
00:29:28,320 --> 00:29:30,080
I said our son would understand,

420
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:32,610
but you've been agonizing over this for days.

421
00:29:33,320 --> 00:29:35,800
Yes, our Qingyun has grown up

422
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,090
and is sensible now.

423
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:39,280
Then,

424
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:40,520
I'll book the flight.

425
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:43,000
Leaving so soon?

426
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:44,280
Yes.

427
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:46,080
I have to go early,

428
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:48,840
otherwise someone else might take the job.

429
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:49,760
By the way,

430
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,090
you and Yuanbao,

431
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:53,660
you must go to school and come back together,

432
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:55,440
so you can look out for each other.

433
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:57,960
And you two need to do your best

434
00:29:58,040 --> 00:29:58,900
and study hard.

435
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:00,960
Don't worry, Dad.

436
00:30:01,440 --> 00:30:02,570
Don't worry, Uncle.

437
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,440
I'll keep an eye on Mutou for you.

438
00:30:06,840 --> 00:30:07,880
So,

439
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,200
it's passed unanimously by our family.

440
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:11,840
Come on,

441
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:13,560
I'll go pack your dad's luggage.

442
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:14,620
You two study hard.

443
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:15,800
Study hard.

444
00:30:17,280 --> 00:30:18,280
Study hard.

445
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:34,360
Mutou, Zhicheng's top brother

446
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:37,280
usually acts like he's afraid of nothing.

447
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:39,760
But knowing his dad is going far away

448
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:41,800
and facing separation,

449
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:43,880
he still acts like a child,

450
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,760
feeling wronged and sad.

451
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:49,600
Is it true that no matter how old someone gets,

452
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:51,680
when facing their parents,

453
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:54,120
they instantly become a child?

454
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,880
What does that feel like?

455
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:59,440
I really want to experience it.
